cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.CY

This paper deals with geographic information retrieval from online data, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) to extract and analyze location information. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to infer the geographic focus of online documents, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Software Engineering). The paper also deals with analyzing social media sharing patterns, which involves techniques from computational linguistics (CL) and cybernetics (CY), making cs.CL and cs.CY likely sub-categories as well.
